.TH NBT\-STATUS 1 "2026-04-15" "truenas-pydiscovery" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nbt\-status \- query registered names on a NetBIOS host
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nbt\-status
.RB [ \-t
.IR TIMEOUT ]
.RB [ \-\-json ]
.I HOST
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nbt\-status
sends a NetBIOS node status query (NBSTAT) to the specified IP
address and prints a table of all registered names with their
types and flags.
Similar to
.BR "nbtstat \-a" .
.PP
No daemon is required.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I HOST
IP address of the host to query.
.TP
.BI \-t " TIMEOUT" "\fR,\fP \-\-timeout " TIMEOUT
Query timeout in seconds.
Default: 2.0.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output as JSONL (one JSON object per registered name).
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
nbt\-status 192.168.1.100
nbt\-status 10.0.0.5 \-\-json
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nbt\-lookup (1),
.BR truenas\-netbiosns (8)
